argument.p:
Caeſar hauing aduertiſement of theſe new troubles;
haſteth into Gallia and prepareth
for the warre.

Caeſar new trimmeth his late ſhaken nauie: the Britaines
ſet vpon the Romans as they harueſted;
but were put off by Caeſar.

The Neruij propound the ſame things to Cicero
which Ambiorix had done to Sabinus;
but are reiected.
